<p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:18pt;color:#008080"><strong>Building Blocks: July 2018</strong></span></p>
<p style="text-align:center"><strong><em>A newsletter for ABCD in Action</em></strong></p>
<p></p>
<p><span style="font-size:14pt"><strong><span style="color:#008080">Learning Opportunities from the ABCD Institute</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt">The ABCD Institute, located at DePaul University, is sponsoring <a href="https://resources.depaul.edu/abcd-institute/news-events/events/Pages/default.aspx" target="_blank">two upcoming learning opportunities</a>.</span></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt"><a href="http://abcdinaction.org/mailer/link/83049/1732" target="_blank">ABCD Institute Training: An Introduction To ABCD</a>, Aurora, Colorado, USA. Sept. 26, 2018</span></p>
</li>
<li><span style="font-size:12pt"><a href="http://abcdinaction.org/mailer/link/83050/1732" target="_blank">ABCD for Faith-Rooted Organizations: Training Opportunity</a>, Chicago IL USA. Oct. 31, 2018</span></li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt">Sign up today for the best registration rates! Scholarship opportunities available. </span></p>
<p></p>
<p><span style="font-size:14pt"><strong><span style="color:#008080">Get Active on ABCD in Action</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt">We&#39;ve had questions from members about how to post on ABCD in Action. So here&#39;s a quick description of what you can do. Begin by logging into the site. Once you have logged in, you&#39;ll automatically go to the main page. Here you can see what&#39;s been happening lately. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt">There&#39;s a lot going on and many opportunities for you to get connected. Most of your posts can be done directly through your own personal profile. So if you want to post photos or videos, announce an event, or share your thoughts in a blog, log into the site and then click on your own name. Use the menu right below your name to post - just click on the type of item you want to post and then follow the directions. Experiment! You can&#39;t break anything here (and if something gets a little messed up, just email us at <a href="mailto:ABCDinAction@gmail.com" target="_blank">ABCDinAction@gmail.com</a> to get it fixed).  </span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt">One exception: You might want to join or start a conversation. <strong>All conversations take place in our <a href="http://abcdinaction.org/mailer/link/83051/1732" target="_blank">Forum</a>.</strong> Click on a post to read and respond to it. Or click on the + sign in any of the forum categories to add a new question or start a new conversation. Again we encourage you to try posting. It&#39;s a great way to make a new connection!</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt"><a href="http://abcdinaction.org/mailer/link/83052/1732" target="_blank">You can find more detailed directions here</a>. And we hope to start sharing videos soon that walk you through the process. So stay tuned!</span></p>
<p></p>
<p><span style="font-size:14pt"><strong><span style="color:#008080">What&#39;s Happening on ABCD in Action?</span></strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt"><em><strong>Blogs:</strong></em> Although you may not have thought about it before, you can blog on ABCD in Action. All members can!  Blogs are a great way to share your thoughts on a particular topic, to tell a story about a how you&#39;re using ABCD, or to highlight what&#39;s been going on in your community.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt">To post a blog, begin by logging in and going to your own profile (click on your name in the menu). Once on your own profile page, click on <strong>Blog</strong> in the menu under your name, and then click on the + sign to open up the blog template. <a href="http://abcdinaction.org/mailer/link/83053/1732" rel="noopener" target="_blank">Questions? Let us know!</a></span></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span style="background-color:rgb(255,242,204)"><a href="http://abcdinaction.org/mailer/link/83054/1732" target="_blank" style="">A<span style="font-size:12pt">sset Mapping World Record in the Netherlands!</span></a><span style="font-size:12pt"> Almost 100 people registered 672 talents, skills and things they want to share with their community in just 15 minutes. Find out how they did it and watch the video, all posted by Eric Hendriks.</span></span></p>
</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt;background-color:rgb(255,242,204)"><em><strong>Forum:</strong></em> The forum is where you can ask questions and engage in conversation. Here are some conversations that were recently added or updated. You can <a href="http://abcdinaction.org/mailer/link/83051/1732" rel="noopener" target="_blank">post your own question on the forum by going here</a>. </span></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt;background-color:rgb(255,242,204)"><a href="http://abcdinaction.org/mailer/link/83055/1732" target="_blank">Interested in Training?</a> We&#39;d like to know what kind of learning opportunities you&#39;re interested in. Are there specific ABCD topics? Would you prefer face-to-face or online? Tell us what you think! </span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt;background-color:rgb(255,242,204)"><a href="http://abcdinaction.org/mailer/link/83056/1732" target="_blank">Intergenerational Asset Mapping in Our Rural Community</a> A diverse group of youth, young adults, olders and elders came together this spring in Duncan, BC, Canada to map our assets.</span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p><span style="font-size:12pt;background-color:rgb(255,242,204)"><a href="http://abcdinaction.org/mailer/link/83057/1732" target="_blank">ABCD As Foundation in Community Inquiry Labs at the Public Library </a> Attention librarians! (and people who love libraries!). Check out this interesting conversation. </span></p>
</li>
